fix(theme): implement three-way toggle and fix auto mode rendering

- Add ThemeMode field to PageData to track user preference separately
  from the resolved CSS class (Theme field is always "dark" or "light")
- Server resolves "auto" cookie → "dark" CSS class with data-theme-mode="auto"
  attribute so CSS can display the correct icon without JS running
- All three layout templates (base, public, admin) now emit data-theme-mode
  attribute on <html> element for CSS-driven icon/label selection
- Add monitor/screen SVG icon for auto mode in both desktop and mobile toggles
- Toggle cycles dark → light → auto → dark per AI.md PART 16 spec
- CSS icon and label selectors updated from html.theme-X class to
  html[data-theme-mode="X"] attribute selectors (supports all three states)
- JS setTheme("auto") resolves to system preference via prefers-color-scheme
  for the CSS class, but stores "auto" in cookie and localStorage
- System theme change listener fires applyTheme when stored mode is "auto"
- Remove duplicate prefers-color-scheme listener (superseded by new one)

